parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

the vehicle stalls
the vehicle is hard to start.

the vehicle struggles to move forward

the vehicle goes into limp mode

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the camshaft and lifters can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Additionally, it can cause damage to the engine and other components, resulting in costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit a ticking or knocking noise
misfire codes
loss of power
stalling

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold bolts can cause exhaust gas leaks, which can lead to carbon monoxide poisoning and other safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit a ticking or knocking noise
exhaust gas leaks

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump relay can cause the fuel pump to continue running even when the engine is turned off, leading to battery drain and potentially causing a fire.
symptoms: The vehicle may exhibit a humming or buzzing noise from the fuel pump
even when the engine is turned off.
